stylometry: When determining safety stock, a manager must consider the EDDLT (estimated demand during lead time) which will indicate how much inventory must be kept on hand while waiting for the next delivery. This can be particularly difficult when you are dealing with uncertain demand since keeping too much inventory on hand while waiting for the next shipment will cause you to incur holding costs, while keeping too little inventory during lead time will cause you to not meet demand and lose sales. Another varible to consider is the length of lead time (if you use a shipment company that comes in 5-10 business days). Having shipments too early will mean that you don't clear out all of your safety stock while shipments coming late may cause a stock out while waiting for them to arrive.
